HEADWORD: Wood-layer
<hw>Wood"-lay`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A young oak, or other timber plant, laid down in a hedge among the
whitethorn or other plants used in hedges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woodless</ent>⟦br⟧
